        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15989",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kingcrunch",
                        "name": "kingcrunch",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Krebs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "split multi-file-based translations into different directories should also be able. A quick&dirty-workaround by me you can see below, if youre interested in. This based on a structure, where the files where place in \/\"locale\"\/myfile.mo.  I think a swap beetween file- and directoryname like \/mydir\/\"locale\".mo should not very difficult. Im thinking about an extension of Zend_Translate to realise this feature internaly by my Translate-Class without setting it up external.\n{code}        $loc = new Zend_Locale();\n        $languageDir = new DirectoryIterator($directory);\n        $translate = null;\n        foreach ($languageDir as $entry) {\n            \/\/Zend_Debug::dump ($entry->getFilename());\n            if ($entry->isDot() || $entry->isFile()) {\n                continue;\n            }\n            if ($loc->isLocale($entry->getFilename())) {\n                $localeDir = new DirectoryIterator(realpath($entry->getPathname()));\n                foreach ($localeDir as $localeEntry) {\n                    if ($localeEntry->isDot() || $localeEntry->isDir()) {\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                    if ($localeEntry->getFilename() === 'myfile.mo') {\n                        if ($translate === null) {\n                            $translate = new Zend_Translate ('gettext', $localeEntry->getPathname(),$entry->getFilename());\n                        } else {\n                            $translate->addTranslation ($localeEntry->getPathname(),$entry->getFilename());\n                        }\n                    }\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n        }{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kingcrunch",
                        "name": "kingcrunch",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Krebs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-26T18:54:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-26T18:54:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16002",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Multi Directory Support is part of ZF-1774 not ZF-1773...\n\nThe needs are quite different as not all are using gettext as adapter.\nFor CSV you would probably use directory only support.",
